            {
                "comment": "One of the best professors (and classes) I have had at UW. The exams are short answer which requires you to have a good understanding of the material so I feel like I learned a lot from. Take good notes in class - exams are open note!  Always willing to meet outside of class to answer questions and chat about his research. Best professor ever!",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "The best bio 151 professor there is no counter argument",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Overall, Dr. Wolman was a good prof. Exams are primarily based off of lecture, so be sure to take good notes and watch online videos if you miss a class. Textbook can be helpful to clarify anything that's confusing. He wants everyone to ace the exam, so if you put in the effort to learn, getting an A on the exam is not unreasonable.",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Dr. Wolman was my least favorite of our three lecturers; he wasn't bad--just not my style. He's a cool guy, but I didn't get much from his forgetful power point  lectures that he flew through, so I relied mostly on the book for his section.",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Professor Wolman was the best lecturer of the three section course. It was the easiest and the most clear to students. He highlighted important points and always responded to emailed questions. As someone with not much background in biology, I felt like he really helped me understand the material unlike the other two professors. Textbook helpful.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
